                    		<p>About older programmers being more expensive: I make 4x what I made when I started out in 1990, but this isn&#8217;t because I&#8217;m 4x as good as I was then.  I have gotten better, but not that much better.  The biggest factor is that now I&#8217;m proven.  It&#8217;s very hard to evaluate programmers without a track record, and that uncertainty is priced in.  Some young hires will turn out to have been an amazing bargain, while others will turn out to have been a waste of money.</p>
