        <div class="comment clearfix " id="comment-245">
            			<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/606328a5c273da9dcaf795e40d5d0537?s=48&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F0.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D48&amp;r=G' class='avatar avatar-48 photo' height='48' width='48' />                    	<p class="comment-details"><em><a href='http://brainbol.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>gines</a></em> | March 16, 2010 at 5:51 pm</p>
                    		
            		<div class="comment-text">
                    		<p>Neurologs of all the world are saying brain is plastic, that means an older man or woman can train their brains at evry age to go as faster as they want. It&#8217;s only a matter of training. The fault is not in the age, the fault is on our educating system that makes you think quick during your first years and then nothing but routine until death.</p>
            		</div>
</div>
